-- Blackstone May Buy Back Southern Cross, Sunday Telegraph Says
-- B y   K a r i   L u n d g r e n
-- 2010-11-28T16:33:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-28/blackstone-may-buy-back-southern-cross-sunday-telegraph-says.html
Blackstone Group LP is considering
buying back  Southern Cross Healthcare Group Plc , the U.K.
nursing home business it sold four years ago, the Sunday
Telegraph said.  One plan the buyout company is considering would be to
merge Southern Cross’ property and operating businesses, the
Telegraph said, citing unidentified sources. Southern Cross,
which has a capacity in it nursing homes of about 37,000 beds,
announced last week the end of takeover talks with TowerBrook
Capital Partners (U.K.) LLP, the newspaper reported.  A spokeswoman for Blackstone didn’t immediately return
calls seeking comment today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Kari Lundgren  in London at 
